In this and the following lines we have a

curious feature of the new age. Naviga- tion, agriculture, the life of towns the arts of civilization generally, are spoken of as marks of a falling away from that primaeval perfection the restoration of which is described as the hope of humanity. No scope seems to be left for human effort and skill.
